sentences: Georgy Anatolevich Doniyakh (Дониях Георгий Анатольевич, 1914–1976) was a Soviet conductor.
He graduated from the Leningrad Conservatory in 1943, and later became director of the Orchestra of the Uzbek SSR.
Dobrynya Nikitich, excerpts – Leningrad Radio Choir and Russian balalaika orchestra Vasiliy Andreev, 1959
